{[#]The game actually started with a Queen's Gambit, but at this height, it
became typical for the Catalan already. White has obvious queenside pressure,
but Black is likely to resist. White played} 24. Ng5 $1 {threatening Nxf7+.
How did he continue after the natural} Red8 25. Bg6 $3 {The fastest way to
transfer the queen to the kingside.} Qe5 {This loses by simple means.} ({After
} 25... fxg6 {Alekhine gives the following lines:} 26. Qg2 Bxb4 27. Qh3+ Kg8
28. Qh7+ Kf8 29. Qh8+ Ke7 30. Qxg7+ Kd6 (30... Ke8 31. Qg8+ Ke7 32. Qf7+ Kd6
33. Qxe6#) 31. Rfd1+ Bd2 32. Rxd2#) 26. Nxf7+ Rxf7 27. Bxf7 Qf5 28. Rfd1 $1
Rxd1+ 29. Rxd1 Qxf7 30. Qxc8 Kh7 31. Qxa6 Qf3 32. Qd3+ 1-0

