{[#]So far the main fight has been about occupying the c6- and the c5-squares.
White used his better coordination for the dynamic} 24. Ne4 $1 {when Black
tried keeping his own with} Nd5 {Your move.} 25. Rxd5 $1 {Eliminating the last
piece defending the kingside.} exd5 (25... Rxc1 {loses the queen to} 26. Rxd8
Rxd8 27. Nf6+ gxf6 28. Qxb7 $18) 26. Nf6+ gxf6 (26... Kh8 {leads to a nice
mating pattern after} 27. Rxc8 Qxc8 28. Qh5 h6 29. Qxf7 $18 {followed by Ng6
mate.}) 27. Qg4+ Kh8 28. Rxc8 Ne6 (28... fxe5 29. Bxe5+ f6 30. Rc7 $18) 29. Nc6
d4 30. Rxf8+ ({The move order} 30. Bxd4 Nxd4 31. Rxf8+ Bxf8 32. Qxd4 $18 {
is even more precise.}) 30... Bxf8 31. Bxd4 Bg7 32. Qf3 {and White converted
his extra pawn.} 1-0

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
